The Chalkwind survey confirmed active undead presence across multiple zones, but Kiess route analysts flagged three types in the archive-adjacent corridor as requiring direct suppression before any recovery operation can proceed: the ironpost route house revenant defending the upper floor, the muster yard requisitions ghost still running emergency-powers inventory protocols, and chalk-ash drift crawlers whose distribution pattern suggests they are responding to something drawing them toward the archive zone. Clear all three so the approach can be reassessed.
Kiess investigators confirm the archive approach corridor is cleared and the emergency-powers activity in the muster yard has stopped generating new undead. Preliminary assessment suggests the warden-commander is sustaining active command authority over the Chalkwind dead from inside the sealed Archive wing — a finding that the Syndic Council's institutional monitors will treat as grounds for a formal interdiction order.
